- ONLY use style values that match the original CSS. These are all in the foler: \_ORIGINAL_FILES. If you don't know what values should be applied, ask me to show you the file, or attribution. Do not remove styles. This needs to look like the original site.
- Use CSS variables where appropriate. Do not make up new variables without my approval.

- Always use the latest version of WordPress.
- Use PHP version 8.0 or higher.
- Use WordPress version 6.8 or higher.
- Use WordPress Coding Standards.
- Use WordPress best practices.
- Use WordPress security best practices.
- Use WordPress performance best practices.
- Use WordPress accessibility best practices.
- Use WordPress internationalization best practices.
- Use WordPress security best practices.
- Use WordPress performance best practices.

- For localization, use the text domain "aera"
- Use appropriate escapes for strings and variables.
- Check for functions and variables before using them.
- Use conditional tags to check for the existence of a feature or a plugin.
- Use namespace "Aera" for functions and classes.

- Custom fields are created using Advanced Custom Fields
- Follow best practices for Advanced Custom Fields

- Backend logic (post types, taxonomies, shortcodes, etc.) should be handled in a plugin
- Frontend logic (templates, styles, scripts, etc.) should be handled in the theme
- Use best practices when enqueuing scripts and styles
